Raising this on behalf of Adobe.  Page rendering takes a huge performance/lag hit for pages within large spaces that make use of the pagetree and children macros.  This also affects large spaces using the Documentation theme.  The slowness is directly attributed to the way both macros decide which pages should be rendered in the list which is visible to the current user.

Given that this particular space has 11000 pages, the pagetree macro takes around 2 minutes to render depending on where you are starting within the tree.

Steps to replicate:
* On EAC trigger autocompelte for links and search for {code}[what{code}
* You will see that a lot of search results appear start with {code}what's...{code}
* Whilst in the autocomplete trigger type ' (so you now have [what' in your autocomplete trigger)
You will now notice that it doesn't search for any pages with an apostrophe

The following macro:

{code}
{jiraissues:url=http://jira.atlassian.com/sr/jira.issueviews:searchrequest-xml/temp/SearchRequest.xml?jqlQuery=project+%3D+RNDR+AND+fixVersion+%3D+%226.0.5%22+ORDER+BY+status+DESC%2C+priority+DESC&tempMax=1000}
{code}

yields this error message:
{code}
Error formatting macro: jiraissues: java.lang.RuntimeException: The value 'RNDR' does not exist for the field 'project'.
{code}

As can be seen in https://extranet.atlassian.com/display/DEV/2010/04/06/Atlassian+Renderer+6.0.5+released

RNDR is a restricted project; When passing username and password using the {{&os_username=MYNAME&os_password=MYPASSWORD}} url parameters, the issues can be rendered just fine.

It appears that the error message is wrong and need to be something like: "'RNDR' is a restricted project. You do not have permission to view it."

Edit: Changed description

