I found this when working on [DASHMACROS-16|https://studio.plugins.atlassian.com/browse/DASHMACROS-16]. If you pass a list of labels to the {{\{space\}}} macro, it does between 1-3 queries per label that you pass in. See {{SpacesListMacro#getSpacesForLabels}}

It should be able to do all of that in a constant number of queries (preferably 1, but not more than 2). Currently such methods (get labels given strings in one query and get spaces given a bunch of labels) don't exist in Confluence so they will need to be added in as part of this too.

