Searching for a term like "cheesething" will not find documents where that word appears like this:

bq. com.atlassian.cheesething=false

Perhaps this is just a misunderstanding - tell me if it is.

When you make a query with the contentbylabel macro as follows:
{code}
{contentbylabel:labels=+phones,nokia,samsung}
{code}
As I understand it the query _should_ be:
{code:sql}
phones AND (nokia OR samsung)
{code}
However it seems that the query Confluence is constructing is: {code}phones AND nokia OR samsung{code}
which produces unexpected results.

There is currently no way for me to get a set of results that reflect the first mentioned query, am I right?

