The edit page form contains both the old version number and old markup, which is redundant. There is no good reason to include the old page markup especially given we also have the version number.

If it is only used on the front end, then it should not be part of the form or should be cleared out before submitting.

This will reduce the likelihood of hitting Tomcat's 2MB post data size limit and slightly speed up the loading and submission time of the edit page.

